<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Takeshita-US     01-11 0155</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Takeshita-US,0159</SECOND>
<HEAD>Report: Takeshita, Bush To Meet In Washington Next Month</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prime Minister Noboru Takeshita will visit
President-elect George Bush in Washington early next month, less
than two weeks after Bush's inauguration, Japanese news reports said
today.
   During his five-day trip starting Jan. 31, Takeshita is also
scheduled to meet with outgoing President Reagan at his California
home, the reports said.
   A Foreign Ministry official said ``discussions are under way''
regarding the trip and an exact itinerary, but declined to confirm
details.
   Takeshita had originally planned to travel to Washington earlier
this month but canceled the trip because of the deteriorating health
of Emperor Hirohito, who died Saturday of intestinal cancer at age
87.
   Takeshita is scheduled to leave for the United States on Jan. 31,
meet with Bush the next day and return home Feb. 4, said Asahi
Shimbun, a major Japanese daily.
   Bush is to be inaugurated Jan. 20.
</TEXT>
