<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Seoul-Population     01-11 0126</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Seoul-Population,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Seoul's Population Totals 10.2 Million</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The population of Seoul totaled 10.28
million people last year, making the South Korean capital the
sixth-largest city in the world, according to a census released
today.
   The census, conducted by the city government in November, showed
the number of people in the capital increased 2.95 percent from 1987
and accounted for one-fourth of the nation's total population.
   The number of foreigners residing in Seoul fell by 4 percent to
10,195 people, the census showed.
   Foreigners residing in Seoul included 3,370 Americans, 3,233
Chinese, 1,513 Japanese and 179 West Germans, according to the
survey.
   The census did not cover the 42,000 U.S. troops stationed in the
city under a defense treaty, officials said.
</TEXT>
