<HEAD>Stocks Close At Record High, Dollar Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices closed at another record high Wednesday
on the Tokyo Stock Exchange, as the U.S. dollar surged against the
Japanese yen.
   The dollar finished at 126.95 yen, up 1.25 yen from Tuesday's
125.70 close. The currency, which opened at 126.68 yen, traded
between 126.48 yen and 126.95 yen.
   The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues, which closed at
a record 31,006.51 points Tuesday, gained another 136.94 points, or
0.44 percent, to finish at 31,143.45 _ another record high.
   Dealers said investors were a little cautious at the start of the
trading day because of the sharp gains so far this week, but added
that the index moved up following buying orders from individual and
foreign investors.
   On the foreign exchange market, the U.S. currency started high in
early trading when ``yen-dollar transactions outpaced those of the
West German mark or the Swiss franc,'' said a dealer with a major
commercial bank in Tokyo, who spoke anonymously.
   He added however that trading was light with only a few
participants in the absence of economic news to affect the market.
</TEXT>
