number clearly.
   ``Then he produced an envelope bearing a badly written note. The
teller got the message and filled it with money,'' Bjornson said.
   There was no sign of a weapon, but the officer quoted a teller as
saying a gun might might have been mentioned in the note during
Monday's heist.
   Poilce were still looking for the culprit early today.
