<FIRST>r i PM-Soviet-EmergencyLanding     01-11 0120</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Soviet-Emergency Landing,0122</SECOND>
<HEAD>Pan Am Jumbo Jet Makes Emergency Landing in Moscow</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Pan Am Boeing 747 flying from Frankfurt to New
Delhi made an emergency landing in Moscow after an oil leak prompted
the crew to shut down one of the four engines, Tass said.
   The airliner was flying over Aktyubinsk in Kazakhstan on Tuesday
night when it developed the oil leak, and it flew 950 miles to
Moscow for the emergency landing, the official news agency reported.
   The jumbo jet, which was carrying more than 300 passengers,
landed without difficulty, Tass said.
   Pan Am sent another plane to Moscow to carry the passengers to
their destination. The repaired plane flew back to Frankfurt today.
</TEXT>
