<HEAD>Seven Villagers Killed in Border Attack</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mozambican rebels opened fire in a
Zimbabwean border village after accusing some residents of opposing
them, killing seven villagers and wounding three, police said
Wednesday.
   Four children were among the dead, a police officer said.
   The Mozambique National Resistance guerrillas penetrated the
remote village about five miles inside Zimbabwe several days ago, he
said. They rounded up some villagers, accused them of acting as
informers, and opened fire, he said.
   Right-wing Mozambican rebels often cross into neighboring
Zimbabwe to steal food and supplies. Scores of Zimbabwean civilians
have been killed in cross-border raids.
