<HEAD>Jurors Chalkboard Notes Alarm Judge, Panel Pleads Innocence</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Jurors whose lives have been on hold for
nearly two years in the McMartin Pre-School molestation trial had
some explaining to do about ominous-looking notes scrawled on a jury
room chalk board.
   ``HUNGJURY,'' ``HANGMAN,'' ``VERDICT,'' ``WASTED,'' ``$10 A DAY''
