<FIRST>r i AM-Obit-Nichols     01-11 0116</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Obit-Nichols,0120</SECOND>
<HEAD>Times of London Correspondent Dies After Long Illness</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Peter Nichols, veteran correspondent in Rome of the
Times of London, died of a stroke Wednesday after a long illness. He
was 61.
   Nichols, a native of Portsmouth, England, reported for the Times
from Italy from 1957 until his retirement a year ago.
   In 1987, Italy honored him with the title ``commendatore of the
republic,'' for his reporting.
   Nichols also wrote several books on Italy and the Vatican.
   Funeral services were scheduled for Friday in Bracciano, a
lakeside town near Rome where the family kept a home. Survivors
include four children from his first marriage and a son from his
second marriage.
</TEXT>
