<HEAD>Renowned Fur Designer Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MILAN, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Jole Veneziani, one of Italy's most renowned
fur designers, has died in her home at the age of 87.
   Veneziani, who died Tuesday, retired from the fashion business
four years ago.
   She was considered one the most popular and innovative designers
in the 1960s and was one of the first to use unusual colors in her
furs.
