<FIRST>r w AM-Reagan-Bush     01-11 0095</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Reagan-Bush,80</SECOND>
<HEAD>Reagan's Advice To Bush: `Get Out Of The Room First'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan had some advice Wednesday for
George Bush, but the president-elect wasn't around to hear it.
   After presenting congressional gold medals to Natan and Avital
Sharansky, Reagan was asked by a reporter if he had any advice for
Bush as prepares to take over the presidency.
   Reagan looked around, noticed that Bush, who attended the
ceremony as vice president, had already stepped outside, and replied:
   ``Keep on doing what he just did. Get out of the room first.''
</TEXT>
