<SECOND>BC-Congressional Pay, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0567,130</SECOND>
<HEAD>With Congressional Perks</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Subs last graf to include month raise took place</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan has recommended raising
congressional pay for rank-and-file lawmakers from $89,500 to
$135,000. Here is the recent history on congressional pay.
   1980 _ House and Senate members were paid $60,662 per year.
   1982 _ House members $69,800 with outside earned income limited
to 30 percent of salary; Senate $60,662.
   1983 _ Senate $69,800 with unlimited outside income. House
remained unchanged.
   1984 _ House and Senate, $72,000; Senate members subject to 30
percent limit on outside earned income.
   1985 _ House and Senate $75,100; Senate raises limit on outside
income to 40 percent of salary.
   1987 _ House and Senate, $77,400 in January; automatic increase
previously voted.
   1987 _ House and Senate, $89,500 in February; House refused to
block a Reagan pay-raise recommendation.
