<FIRST>r a AM-Obit-DuVal-Lewis     01-11 0157</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Obit-DuVal-Lewis,0162</SECOND>
<HEAD>Granddaughter of Benjamin Harrison Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TUCSON, Ariz. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Irene DuVal-Lewis, a granddaughter of
President Benjamin Harrison and a niece of the French pirate Jean
Lafitte, has died. She was 105.
   She died Monday of natural causes at Park Villa Convalescent
Center, where she had lived since November. Before that, she lived
at La Hacienda Nursing Home.
   Asked recently whether she recalled the White House days in
1889-93 when Harrison was president, Mrs. DuVal-Lewis replied
playfully, ``I lived there, you silly fool.''
   Mrs. DuVal-Lewis said her father, Harvey DuVal, was a colonel in
the Confederate Army.
   She was born Nov. 13, 1883, in Tallahassee, Fla., and spent most
of her life in Florida. She was a Red Cross volunteer for 50 years.
Her husband died eight years ago.
   Mrs. DuVal-Lewis is survived by a great-niece, two grandchildren
and one great-grandchild. Records indicate she outlived a child, two
brothers and a sister. Services were pending.
