<HEAD>T-Bills Up In Wednesday's Auction</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on seven-year Treasury notes rose in
Wednesday's auction to the highest level in 15 months.
   The average yield was 9.30 percent, up from 8.73 percent at the
last auction on Oct. 12.
   It was the highest rate since seven-year notes averaged 9.51
percent on Oct. 7, 1987. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate
of 9\ percent with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,974.70.
   A total of $7.02 billion in notes were sold out of bids totalling
$22.6 billion.
