<DATELINE>FRANKFURT, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fire broke out Wednesday in a
hotel used mainly for housing Third World asylum seekers, injuring
five people, the city fire brigade chief said.
   Three residents of the hotel, located one block from Frankfurt's
main train station, fled to the building's roof as flames spread to
the top floor of the six-story structure. They were recued by
firefighters using long ladders.
