<HEAD>Four Killed In Peshawar Bomb Explosion</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PESHAWAR, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bomb explosion in an auto repair shop
killed four people and wounded 13 on Wednesday in the old quarter of
this frontier city, less than 30 miles from Afghanistan, a police
spokesman said.
   Police said nearby buildings were heavily damaged.
   No one claimed responsibility, but government officials, speaking
on condition of anonymity, blamed agents of the Marxist Afghan
government.
   Pakistan harbors more than 3 million Afghan war refugees and acts
as a conduit for weapons to U.S.-backed Islamic guerrillas fighting
the Soviet-supported government in Kabul.
