<FIRST>r a AM-People-Quaid     01-11 0356</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-People-Quaid,0366</SECOND>
<HEAD>Dennis Quaid Still May Sing In Jerry Lee Lewis Role As Film Crew
Moves On</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By WOODY BAIRD</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rock 'n' roller Jerry Lee Lewis will
perform most of his music on the soundtrack for a movie about his
life, but actor Dennis Quaid will likely get in on some of the
singing too, a producer said Wednesday.
   ``I'm hoping Dennis might sing a Jerry Lee Lewis song, one or
two,'' producer Adam Fields said as his film crews wrapped up work
in Memphis and prepared to leave for London.
   The movie, ``Great Balls of Fire,'' is based on Lewis' early
recording career in the '50s. Quaid portrays Lewis.
   Filming began in Memphis in October and Lewis said than that he
planned to provide the music for the movie and soundtrack while
Quaid would handle the acting.
   Quaid, who sings with a rock 'n' roll band of his own and plays
the guitar and piano, will handle some of the musical chores in the
film and on the record album that spins from it, Fields said.
   ``The majority of the music in the picture is Jerry Lee's track,
but we've got a long haul until post production,'' he said. ``I hope
to have some of Dennis on the album.''
   Lewis will do all the piano playing, Fields said.
   ``There's only one Jerry Lee, God bless him,'' he said. ``That's
why he's the last of the living legends.''
   The album, with a variety of music from the movie, will include
songs played in barrooms Lewis visited in the early `50s, several of
his first big hits, and even some gospel tunes that influenced him,
Fields said.
   Tom Gray, a spokesman for the movie, said cast and crew members
were getting ready to leave for London, the other main locale of the
movie, which is scheduled to be released in July.
   Lewis was forced to leave England during a tour when he was 23
because of a public outcry over his then-recent marriage to his
13-year-old cousin, Myra. They were divorced in 1971. Lewis has been
married six times.
</TEXT>
