<HEAD>London Shares Close Slightly Lower</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDS: RECASTS throughout to UPDATE with later activity, closing index;
No pickup</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices closed slightly lower Wednesday on the
London Stock Exchange, hit by a bout of profit-taking following
strong gains made in the last five trading sessions.
   At the close, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index
was down 1.9 points, or 0.1 percent, at 1,834.1. The index fell as
much as 5.6 points in the afternoon, following concerted
intervention by major central banks to knock the dollar lower on
foreign-exchange markets, dealers said.
   But a strong opening on Wall Street helped London shares recover
from their worst levels. At its best, the 100-share index was down
just 0.8 point at midafternoon.
   The Financial Times 30-share index ended with a loss of 4.7
points at 1,498.8.
   The Financial Times 500-share index fell 0.66 point to close at
1,032.87.
   Volume was moderate, edging up to 581.3 million shares from 563.5
million traded on Tuesday.
