   As measured by Wilshire Associates' index of more than 5,000
actively traded stocks, the market increased $12.27 billion, or 0.44
percent, in value.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks added
.80 to 158.65.
   Standard &amp; Poor's industrial index rose 1.96 to 326.29, and S&amp;P's
