<FIRST>u f AM-AutoIncentives     01-11 0203</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Auto Incentives,0209</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ford Extends Incentives</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DEARBORN, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co. on Wednesday offered
low-interest financing and extended cash-back rebates on some of its
1988 and 1989 cars and trucks.
   The company also offered special deals for Mercury Tracer buyers
in California, where import competition is particularly stiff.
   Ford said in a news release that a nationwide financing plan with
interest as low as 4.9 percent, depending on the term of the loan,
will be offered through March 2 on some cars and trucks. Buyers have
an option on those vehicles of taking cash rebates ranging from $400
to $750.
   California residents who buy a Tracer, which competes with small
foreign cars, will have the chance through March 2 of taking a 3.9
percent financing deal.
   Also in California, the company began offering $300 in cash to
existing rebate programs for buyers of 1988 and 1989 Ford Taurus and
Mercury Sable cars with 3.8-liter, six-cylinder engines. That rebate
was created because of larger-than-anticipated supplies of those
cars, Ford spokesman Bill Carroll said.
   In addition, Ford said it was extending until March 2 rebate
offers scheduled to expire Thursday for a variety of cars and trucks
ranging from $400 to $3,000.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
